                            <comment id="12656336" author="stack" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2008 21:41:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For 0.19.0, minimally make sure that our timeouts are at least defaults of hdfs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12657305" author="stack" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2008 06:56:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I reviewed datanode and namenode configurations.  It heartbeats every 3 seconds.  Retries 3 times.  Doesn&apos;t have notion of shutting down if doesn&apos;t connect to master as we do.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closing as invalid.  When ZK is in the mix, I think we&apos;ll be less fragile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
